text.text:
Q1.
Could you introduce yourself and your experience in the Blockchain industry, highlight your team's skills for BitmapValley success,¬† and share the story behind Bitmap Valley's creation, including the timeline and motivation?

text_entities.text:
Q1.
Could you introduce yourself and your experience in the Blockchain industry, highlight your team's skills for BitmapValley success,¬† and share the story behind Bitmap Valley's creation, including the timeline and motivation?

messages.text:
My name is Chris and I‚Äôve been in the space a very long time, originally as a miner, then trader, and now founder.

We have created a lot of things for the Solana blockchain, too many to go over here but we‚Äôve also created the first of its kind ‚Äúmetaverse as a service‚Äù platform using the Bitcoin blockchain.

Moving forward I will refer to Bitmap Valley as ‚ÄúBMV‚Äù.

BMV is the first ‚Äúnon-arbitray‚Äù metaverse product ever created and all the important data that is used to construct this world is derived from Bitcoin block data using an inscription  known as ‚Äúbitmaps‚Äù

The alpha product already exists and we have a ton of updates coming for what we call "phase 2" that will be released along side our upcoming token drop on Bitcoin using the newest token standard called "Runes"

Ultimately we are using all of our experience to create a product on bitcoin that most ppl told us was not possible, we've proven them wrong.

text.text:
Q2.
Now said to be the first composable 3D metaverse product that uses bitmap data to offer metaverse as a service on BTC. Give us an introduction into your Ecosystem, products & services. What is your mission and vision for the future, what problems are you hoping to solve?

text_entities.text:
Q2.
Now said to be the first composable 3D metaverse product that uses bitmap data to offer metaverse as a service on BTC. Give us an introduction into your Ecosystem, products & services. What is your mission and vision for the future, what problems are you hoping to solve?

messages.text:
Basically "composability" to us means that you can adapt any "type" of experience within the framework of "BMV" we are very proud to say that any functions we could create on blockchains that use "smart contracts" we've been able to do similarly on bitcoin using our game engine to create logic that performs like "smart contracts"

We also can scale this product into all the bitmaps that currently exist and will exist by creating the most affordable, lowest barrier to entry product possible.

Currently personalization, social experiences, and game loops that offere reward structures, incentives for onboarding, tournaments, community events etc can all take place from "BMV"

We also have the ability to use these districts to provide utility and social experiences for other projects including mini games that can add value to their assets and tokens as well.

This is what "composable" means to us, we can fit any need or narrative using our game engine and the bitcoin blockchain as our "verification layer".

text:
IMSO Chris (Bitmap Valley):
Lowest barrier to entry by far, our public district sales that go live soon require you to have less than $100 + a bitmap to create your own "district" which is generated using the bitmap data you chose during the "claim" process.

This metaverse product is more of a "social platform" that offers "mini games" along with a ton of other options that is geared toward offereing projects and users opportunities to create their own value in a multitude of ways,  there are dozens of opportunities for people to become profitable inside of bitmap valley with very little experience needed.

Also BMV is limited in size do to the number of bitcoin blocks that exist, if you look at Sandbox or other products you'll notice they "make up" the numbers for everything in their worlds, we do not.

We can only create districts if there is a bitmap present and our metaverse only gets larger as more bitcoin blocks are produced, we can also support all bitmaps in existence (over 800k of them) with no problem which makes us the most "scalable"

Right now you can browse the alpha version of the "town square" via
or you can check out a live district that was created using 313377.bitmap by add

to the end of the URL. 

This is all about 4 months old since our last update, this month we will be adding hundreds of new items and dozens of features to the BMV product.

Q1)
What is the primary function, total supply, and utility proposition of the Me3 token, including its role in empowering users, facilitating decentralized governance, and providing additional value to the ecosystem?

text_entities.text:
Q1)
What is the primary function, total supply, and utility proposition of the Me3 token, including its role in empowering users, facilitating decentralized governance, and providing additional value to the ecosystem?
I‚Äôll take it
@volpyprocdump
üëåüèº

messages.text: The Me3 token acts as the fundamental governance and, to some extent, utility token within the Me3 ecosystem. Its primary role is to steer and bolster the Stake to Win platform, akin to how DeFi governance tokens operate by motivating governance involvement. This is achieved through the conversion of platform earnings into token rewards, which are subsequently distributed among governance participants. There is a total supply of 1,000,000,000 tokens and a projected fully diluted market cap of US$12,000,000.00 ($12M) upon public listing.

text_entities.text: The Me3 token acts as the fundamental governance and, to some extent, utility token within the Me3 ecosystem. Its primary role is to steer and bolster the Stake to Win platform, akin to how DeFi governance tokens operate by motivating governance involvement. This is achieved through the conversion of platform earnings into token rewards, which are subsequently distributed among governance participants. There is a total supply of 1,000,000,000 tokens and a projected fully diluted market cap of US$12,000,000.00 ($12M) upon public listing.

messages.text: The Me3 token empowers users within the Me3 ecosystem by granting them the right to propose and actively participate in decision-making processes. Through this decentralized governance structure, Me3 community members can collectively shape the ecosystem.

text_entities.text: The Me3 token empowers users within the Me3 ecosystem by granting them the right to propose and actively participate in decision-making processes. Through this decentralized governance structure, Me3 community members can collectively shape the ecosystem.

messages.text: To engage in governance within the Me3 ecosystem, users must acquire voting power, a privilege secured by staking Me3 tokens. This voting power allows users to influence important decisions, such as the determination of critical platform fees and selecting strategic partnerships that will receive Me3 token financing. We think this will hold significant appeal for users, as the ecosystem partners we target are oftentimes prominent and publicly recognized brands. Strong working with Strong üí™üèº

text: Good question! I'll break it down into two parts

text_entities.text: @Ravi1237
Good question! I'll break it down into two parts

messages.text: By holding Me3 tokens, users gain fee discounts across the platform. This presents a benefit, as platform fees commonly arise when swapping, purchasing cryptocurrencies, as well as off-ramping funds, and when initiating token pools using the "support to win" feature.

text_entities.text: By holding Me3 tokens, users gain fee discounts across the platform. This presents a benefit, as platform fees commonly arise when swapping, purchasing cryptocurrencies, as well as off-ramping funds, and when initiating token pools using the "support to win" feature.

messages.text: The extent of the fee discount directly correlates with the quantity of Me3 tokens held by the user, incentivizing longer token holding periods (or in other words lower token velocity), which in turn bolster the token's value.

text_entities.text: The extent of the fee discount directly correlates with the quantity of Me3 tokens held by the user, incentivizing longer token holding periods (or in other words lower token velocity), which in turn bolster the token's value.

messages.text: The fee discount mechanism further ensures that as the Me3 ecosystem grows and transaction volume increases, so will the demand for the Me3 token, positioning it as a beneficiary of the ecosystem's expansion.

text_entities.text: The fee discount mechanism further ensures that as the Me3 ecosystem grows and transaction volume increases, so will the demand for the Me3 token, positioning it as a beneficiary of the ecosystem's expansion.

messages.text: Secondly, Me3 token holders can stake their token and earn up to 50% of the platform fees generated through Me3's various solutions. Similar fee sharing mechanisms are implemented by established NFT marketplaces, such as LooksRare of X2Y2 - although often boosted by emission-based token rewards.

messages.text: In comparison to the aforementioned fee discounts, which incentivize Me3 users to hold tokens, token staking presents a strong utility to users and non-users alike. This enlarges the potential holder (staker) base of the Me3 token as anyone that wants to benefit from the growth of the Me3 ecosystem can purchase and stake their tokens for an extended period of time.

messages.text:
We can initially give users from any chain an opportunity to be particiapants in our bitcoin native product, later we can allow the use of tokens from other chains (specifically the ME3 token) and then ultimately create this seemless experience where no matter what chain or token standard you prefer it can be integrated/utilized in some capacity with our product.

We believe in the immutable and historical nature of BTC, but we also believe in providing new utilities and experiences for users across all chains.

We think that partnering with ME3 will give us an opportunity to serve more users and create new economies from all over the world.

Currently our two main audiences are USA & China.

We hope to also bring users that have not used ME3 into the ME3 ecosystem by providing as mentioned above "lowest barrier to entry"

messages.text: Me3 as an ecosystem will develop as a fan-centric Stake to Win platform. That means enabling fans to not only  participate in but also set up their own stake to win pools for their favorite teams and competitions.

text_entities.text: Me3 as an ecosystem will develop as a fan-centric Stake to Win platform. That means enabling fans to not only  participate in but also set up their own stake to win pools for their favorite teams and competitions.

messages.text: As such we are more about empowering users and following the community to develop new features and pools. We are implementing a DAO based feedback system that guides the scale and breadth of the pools offered as well as the rules around participating in those pools.

messages.text:
Success in the Hype Pool is measured by a comprehensive set of criteria designed to capture the essence of community engagement and commitment:

-The total amount raised in support of each team.
-The number of unique user wallet addresses contributing, with a minimum commitment set at $10 USD equivalent, showcasing widespread community backing.
-Social media engagement metrics, including new Twitter followers, Telegram channel joiners, and Discord server participants, all tracked from the point of registration.
-The virality of the campaign, assessed through reposts of official tweets by registered accounts.

Success in the Hype Pool is measured by a comprehensive set of criteria designed to capture the essence of community engagement and commitment:

-The total amount raised in support of each team.
-The number of unique user wallet addresses contributing, with a minimum commitment set at $10 USD equivalent, showcasing widespread community backing.
-Social media engagement metrics, including new Twitter followers, Telegram channel joiners, and Discord server participants, all tracked from the point of registration.
-The virality of the campaign, assessed through reposts of official tweets by registered accounts.

messages.from: Blockchain Ravi [ Will Never DM First ]
messages.text: By holding Me3 tokens, users gain fee discounts across the platform. This presents a benefit, as platform fees commonly arise when swapping, purchasing cryptocurrencies, as well as off-ramping funds, and when initiating token pools using the "Stake to win" feature.

text_entities.text: By holding Me3 tokens, users gain fee discounts across the platform. This presents a benefit, as platform fees commonly arise when swapping, purchasing cryptocurrencies, as well as off-ramping funds, and when initiating token pools using the "Stake to win" feature.

messages.from: Blockchain Ravi [ Will Never DM First ]
messages.text: Secondly, Me3 token holders can stake their token and earn up to 50% of the platform fees generated through Me3's various solutions.

text_entities.text: Secondly, Me3 token holders can stake their token and earn up to 50% of the platform fees generated through Me3's various solutions.

messages.from: Blockchain Ravi [ Will Never DM First ]
messages.text: Similar fee sharing mechanisms are implemented by established NFT marketplaces, such as LooksRare of X2Y2 - although often boosted by emission-based token rewards. In comparison to the aforementioned fee discounts, which incentivize Me3 users to hold tokens, token staking presents a strong utility to users and non-users alike. This enlarges the potential holder (staker) base of the Me3 token as anyone that wants to benefit from the growth of the Me3 ecosystem can purchase and stake their tokens for an extended period of time.
